Executive Profile
Kelly W. Hoffman  Chief Executive Officer and Director, Ring Energy, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships59$939,283As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Kelly W. Hoffman has been the Chief Executive Officer of Ring Energy, Inc. since January 1, 2013. Mr. Hoffman served as the Chief Executive Director and President of VPR Corp. from April 2009 to December 2011. Mr. Hoffman founded Varsity Media Group Inc. in 1991 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from 1998 to November 2009. Mr. Hoffman founded Innovo Group, Inc. in 1998. In the early 1990s Mr. Hoffman co-founded AOCO and began acquiring properties in West ... Texas. In 1996 he arranged financing and purchased 10,000 acres in the Fuhrman Mascho field in Andrews, Texas. In the first six months he organized a 60 well drilling and completion program resulting in a 600% increase in revenue and approximately 18 months later sold the properties to Lomak (Range Resources). In 1999 he again arranged financing and acquired 12,000 acres in Lubbock and Crosby counties. Mr. Hoffman served as the Chief Executive Officer at Varsity Television Inc. From April 2008 to December 2011, Mr. Hoffman served as President of Victory Park Resources. From 1989 to 1991, Mr. Hoffman served in a similar position for Texakoma Financial, an oil and gas partnership that raised capital for acquisition of property in Texas, Louisiana and New Mexico. Prior to that, Mr. Hoffman served in various sales and marketing positions for PAZ Syndicate, a conglomerate based in Tel Aviv, Israel that owned diverse interests worldwide. He specialized in securing capital from investors for investment in various limited partnerships for the oil and gas industry for Paso Energy. He began his career in the Permian Basin in 1975 with Amoco Production Company. Mr. Hoffman serves as Chairman of Varsity Television Inc. Mr. Hoffman served as Chairman of Varsity Media Group Inc. from 1998 to September 2009. He has been an Independent Director of Differential Brands Group Inc. since June 2004. He has been a Director of Ring Energy, Inc. since January 2013. He served as Director of Joe's Jeans Inc. (alternate name is Innovo Group Inc.) since June 2004. Mr. Hoffman attended Texas Tech University and majored in Business Administration.Read Full Background




